Alverson, Luke E.
Associate
 Practice Emphasis:Corporate
 Phone:214-922-4127
 Email:
This e-mail address is being protected from spam bots, you need JavaScript enabled to view it
 Mr. Alverson’s primary practice area is corporate finance and securities law, and he assists clients with matters ranging from initial business formation, counseling, and capital raising, to highly complex mergers and acquisitions, registered securities offering and SEC compliance. Mr. Alverson represented an energy company in a $450 million merger acquisition of a strategic competitor and a publicly-traded master limited partnership in an acquisition of refined product pipelines and terminals and related financings, including a $150 million Rule 144A offering of senior notes and related A/B exchange offer for registered notes. He also represented a regional property and casualty insurance company in its $96 million initial public offering and a public commincation managment company’s $127 million merger with a private software and services provider.
Distinctions
 Author: Sarbanes-Oxley § 302 & 906: Corporate Reform or Legislative Redundancy? A Critical Look at the “New” Corporate Responsibility For Financial Reports, 33 Sec. Reg. L. J. 4, 15-46 (2005).
Note, “Racial Discrimination – The Burden-Shifting Analysis in a Motion for Summary Judgment – The Ninth Circuit Court of Appeals Changes the Supreme Court’s Burden of Production on a Defendant’s Offer of Non-Discrimination: Simmons v. American Airlines,” 68 J. Air L. & Com. 623 (2003).
Admissions
 Texas 2004
 Memberships
 State Bar of Texas, Dallas Bar Association
 Legal Education
 Southern Methodist University School of Law, J.D. magna cum laude, 2004 (Hatton W. Sumners Scholar; Order of the Coif; Finalist, Steinberg Securities Law Scholarship; SMU Law Review – Corporate Counsel Associate Symposium Editor)
Undergraduate Education
 Abilene Christian University, B.B.A. in finance and accounting, summa cum laude, 2000 (Academic Excellence Award Recipient; NCAA All-American and Academic All-American – Golf; MasterCard Post-Graduate Scholarship recipient)


